         <abstract>
            <ab>
             The Maṣḥafa qandil is the ritual for the Unction of the Sick in the Ethiopian Church. Each of its seven sections consists of the following elements:
             the lighting of a wick, a supplication, an epistle, the Trisagion, the Prayer of the Gospel with incensing and a <foreign xml:lang="gez">mǝsbak</foreign>, a Gospel reading and a prayer.
               <ref type="mss" corresp="BNFet78#ms_i1"/> and the liturgical editions   
               <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Tasfa1993Mashafa"/>  
               </bibl> and <bibl> 
                  <ptr target="bm:TasfaQandil"/>   
               </bibl>   agree more or less with each other. 
               <bibl> 
                  <ptr target="bm:Zanetti2010Qandil"/>  
               </bibl>
            </ab>
         </abstract>
